poi.name: Zombie Warrior
poi.notes: There's this gigantic crater and in the middle live some shitty zombies. Even the Mirdain structure on the northeast is empty. How utterly disappointing.

poi.name: Ogre Bully
poi.notes: May no longer exist? If you see this mob, tell Geck.

poi.name: Kobold Scrapper
poi.notes: Downgraded spawn used to be snowclan hunters.

poi.name: Dark Dragon
poi.notes: Spawns under the giant floating island.

poi.name: Malaut Acolyte
poi.notes: Nice spot to farm while waiting for the menhir to the north.

poi.name: Serpentine
poi.notes: In Fluffy's lair, next to the Theyril chest.

poi.name: Fire Elemental
poi.notes: On a large plateau between several spires. Sheer cliff on many sides.

poi.name: Infernal
poi.notes: Devil in the crazy building with weird demonic shit inside. Spawns every 3 hours or something.

poi.name: Greater Matayin
poi.notes: Spawns above water on the island, lol.

poi.name: Lava Golem
poi.notes: Linked to the spawn to the northwest.

poi.name: Lava Golem
poi.notes: Linked to the spawn to the southeast.

poi.name: Teneland
poi.notes: Farm. Usually empty. Good place to bank after hitting up the center of Cairn.

poi.name: Anjir
poi.notes: Quarry. Hamlet on an island inside of a cave.

poi.name: Wilderness Bank
poi.notes: Used to be in a floating hut but now it's in a small fortification on land. There is a merchant and an NPC who offers various quests.

poi.name: Tughri
poi.notes: Elven city on a plateau. Surrounding water and cliff can make escape slow. Bank is on the south side near the grove and farm. Resources: Grove, Farm

poi.name: Serruk
poi.notes: Coastal city is an easy target for naval assaults and hell to defend against if navy is substantial. Bank area is partitioned off on the north side with the farm. Workbench is ridiculously far from the bank. Resources: Mine (Veilron/Selentine), Quarry, Farm, Shipyard, Wonder

poi.name: Izkand
poi.notes: Confusing city with no less than EIGHT gates. Walls everywhere. No free entry. Follow the bindstone glow to the bank. Resources: Grove, Farm, Quarry, Foundry

poi.name: Calfardar
poi.notes: Extremely long and potentially deadly elevator ride up. Elevator makes one stop at a lower level before arriving at the city proper. Be ready to hop over the north wall for a quick approach to the bank. Resources: Farm, Quarry

poi.name: Khayud
poi.notes: It has a farm. That's it. Resources: Farm

poi.name: Gulghat
poi.notes: Easy to defend city with a simple layout. No free entry over any point of the walls. Somewhat susceptible to naval assaults from the south. Resources: Mine (Veilron/Selentine), Grove

poi.name: Alberworth
poi.notes: Very compact city. Crafting stations within spitting range from the bank. Mountain to the south is close enough to focus nuke the bank. Resources: Mine (Leenspar/Neithal), Farm, Quarry, Shipyard, Wonder

poi.name: Dayer
poi.notes: Three layers of walls to get over. Hug the right side and head in through the cave for direct access to the theyril mine and then the bank room. Resources: Mine (Theyril), Farm

poi.name: Telpac
poi.notes: Bank room is in a cave under the eastern mountain. Ranged attacks from one of the many mountains is fun as it is somewhat difficult for the defenders to get on the mountains from inside the city but easy for attackers to get on from the outside. Resources: Mine (Theyril), Grove, Farm, Quarry, Shipyard, Wonder

poi.name: Apautan
poi.notes: Elevator on the north side outside of the walls is an easy entry into the city. Once you go down, the only way back up is through one of the three elevators. Retreats can be difficult in this maze-like city. Resources: Grove, Mine (Neithal/Leenspar)

poi.name: Laurgul
poi.notes: [TT Village] Geck Zilla, Melgaroth Sanddon, Kel Bray

poi.name: Bjonlmir
poi.notes:
[TT Village] Suminabeach Virtus
This place is Timber City. Also has a lot of gardens.

poi.name: Baslan's Escape
poi.notes: 110g per tick, not worth taking at this point in time. Good candidate for new housing plots in upcoming patch.

poi.name: Jamukar's Fall
poi.notes: Possibly the most isolated village in the game.

poi.name: Matayin
poi.notes: They hide in the water just near the shore and confuse you.

poi.name: Hintenfau
poi.notes: One of the most dangerous chaos cities in the game due to its proximity to the center dungeon and the cancer spot.

poi.name: Simiran
poi.notes: The only Chaos city on Cairn. Pretty fun place.

poi.name: Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes: Repeatable quest: Kill 25 shadow spirits for 2k gold and random reward. Known rewards: 5 numen, 100 bone ................................................................................. 2 Sandstone golems at the bottom! Lots of great skinnables here and very active dungeon. Veilron chest is in a side room in the shadow spirit area.

poi.name: Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes: Repeatable quest: Kill 15 cave hags for 3.5k gold and random reward. Known random rewards: 25 panacea, 250 arrows, 30 ancient quintessence [q3 quintessence] ............................................................................... Two rooms with the cave hags, bottom one has about 7 hags in it possibly all cave hags at once. Be careful.

poi.name: Neithal Dungeon
poi.notes: Ork executioner drops goreaxes and executioner's axes 100% of the time and protects the neithal chest. Can get hairy in there if all chieftans spawn.

poi.name: Dungeon
poi.notes: Two spawns of snowclan warriors and snowclan elders. Both have 5 mobs and a 6 minute respawn.

poi.name: Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes: Repeatable Quest, kill 25 darkweavers for 2k gold and random reward. Two cave spider rooms with 3-4 cave spiders and two sarlid rooms with 5-7 sarlids.

poi.name: Leenspar Dungeon
poi.notes: Repeatable quest to kill 40 cave trolls for 1k gold and a random reward. Leenspar chest guarded by Evil Eyes.

poi.name: Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes: Very little of interest here. The chest is on the middle platform near the exit, which is just at the end of a one way dungeon.

poi.name: Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes: Three spawns: 9 pirates, 3 frostwalkers, 7 menhir. Veilron chest is now sitting next to the ship instead of inside.

poi.name: Neithal Dungeon
poi.notes: 3 spawns of snowclans, all mixed... about 5-7 at each spawn. Needs 2 people at a spawn to clear efficiently.

poi.name: Leenspar & Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes: Two Fire Scourges guard the leenspar chest. The Veilron chest is down the hallway in a small cell past the spiral staircase but before the lava room. Exit in the lava room.

poi.name: Neithal Dungeon
poi.notes: Has a room with 4 assassins/maulers, a big chamber with 2 executioners, 2 chieftains, and 4 assassins/maulers. Big room has the neithal chest.

poi.name: Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes: No quest but a nice Summoner / Nightaxe / General / Doombringer spawn right near the exit. There is another spawn like it but it's not near the exit.

poi.name: Double Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes:
Quest to kill 25 shade salamanders for 2k gold and a random reward.
Two Veilron chests. One is on the far east side with the crypt guards and the other is on the far west side with the cave hags.

poi.name: Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes: Very small dungeon, only one room. Nonstop goblin shamans and a food crate. Annoying brittle skeletons and zombie shamblers also spawn.

poi.name: Neithal Dungeon
poi.notes: Three rooms with arthain are easier. The room with the neithal chest has 4 Gravelords and 5 Bone Spiders in it. The 5 Bone Spiders are actually a great way to collect undeath sparkstone.

poi.name: Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes: Quest to kill 15 undead dwarves for 2000 gold and a random reward. I got 300 arrows for my reward. There's a food crate near the quest giver. Lots of iron nodes in the mob spawns. Veilron chest is in the room with 3 Windgraives. Very nice room of Generals and Summoners at the bottom of the dungeon near the exit.

poi.name: Greater Matayin
poi.notes: They're really deep down in the lake there. Pretty annoying.

poi.name: Gargantua
poi.notes: New Gargantua spawn. Has 6-7 Deadeye and Shroud Knight guarding him.

poi.name: Leenspar & Neithal Dungeon
poi.notes: Four Evil Eyes guard the leenspar chest. The Gray Ork Executioner guards the neithal chest. Lots of Gray Orks. Oddly, there is a room with 8 or so zombies in it just past the Evil Eyes and Oathlieges. Exit is at the end of the weird water platforms.

poi.name: Veilron + Neithal Dungeon
poi.notes: Repeatable quest: Kill 30 cave spiders for 3k gold and random reward. Known random rewards: 75 cheese, 75 potatoes, 50 ore, 100 timber, 100 ashes, 150 bone, 100 resin ................................................................................. Veilron chest in a cave at the spider spawn. Neithal chest in the oathliege side room in a bookshelf.

poi.name: Veilron Dungeon
poi.notes: There is a quest to kill cave hags. Veilron chest is in one of the rooms with the cave hags.

poi.name: Icejarl
poi.notes: They will chase you almost all the way to the gate of White View.

poi.name: Veilron Chest
poi.notes: It's in a cave guarded by some dwarf mobs.

poi.name: Veilron Chest
poi.notes: Once upon a time, this was a neithal chest. Then one day they decided to take all the neithal chests out of the game and this turned into a veilron chest.

poi.name: Gorra Dar
poi.notes: About 5 slaves and only one Gorra Dar on a long respawn timer. Gorra Dar is hard.

poi.name: Deadeye
poi.notes: Used to be cairn giants before Oct 2010 patch

poi.name: Oak Lord
poi.notes: Wood and timber factory. Note this is a 2 spawn of Oak Lords. The rest of the mobs are Heielhims.

poi.name: Sea Serpent
poi.notes: At least 2 sea serpents. Unknown number of sharks.

poi.name: Bonecrew Mutineer
poi.notes: Linked to the other two spawns on the island.

poi.name: Theyril Chest
poi.notes: On the black spire, guarded by 6 Serpentine and Fluffy.

poi.name: Serpentine
poi.notes: Up on the big black spire. There's a ramp going up. Watch out for Fluffy.

poi.name: Fire Dragon
poi.notes: Stay at least 1 kilometer away from this spawn point.

poi.name: Blood Achrid
poi.notes: Linked with the nearby Blood Achrid spawn to the east.

poi.name: Neithal Dungeon
poi.notes: Quest to kill 10 Tomb Iklits for 4000 gold and a random reward.

poi.name: Skeleton Warrior
poi.notes: There is one mob here. ONE. This is the worst spawn in the entire game.

poi.name: Dire Spider
poi.notes: They guard the south cave entrance to Ul'Hamra.

poi.name: Night Iklit
poi.notes: In and around a cave. Only at night.

poi.name: Goblin Fighter
poi.notes: It's the newb elf area. What do you expect?

poi.name: Hobbit Village
poi.notes: There's no mobs here. It's pretty well hidden but there is a path with rocks that leads up to it. It's the cutest thing you will ever see in Darkfall. Most people will never lay eyes on it because it is fairly secluded and difficult to chance upon.

poi.name: Air Elemental
poi.notes: Wow, air elementals really do exist.

poi.name: Hill Giant Slugger
poi.notes: Once upon a time, these were Cairn Giants.

poi.name: Thainlich
poi.notes: Thainliches up top. Thainguards down on the ground.

poi.name: Giant Skeleton
poi.notes: This spawn is inside of a giant cave. The entrance is in the nearby giant skeleton spawn on the east side of the volcano.

poi.name: Skeleton Archer
poi.notes: Inside the cave. Entrance is on the east side of the volcano.

poi.name: Matayin
poi.notes: NOTE: This spawn of matayins is entirely submerged in a cave system under the island. It is impossible to skin them because the graves land on the lake bed.

poi.name: Outpost
poi.notes: One guard tower, a merchant named Borr, and I assume a quest giver named Magnus Forkbeard.
